#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_frame.htm%2Bhtml.body.h1:17-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\creating_a_frame.htm+html.body.h1:17-1"
msgid "Creating a Frame"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_frame.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:19-1
msgid ""
"With the JAWS cursor, navigate to the top, left corner of the area you want "
"included in the frame."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_frame.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:20-1
msgid "Press <b>CTRL+SHIFT+LEFT BRACKET</b>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_frame.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:21-1
msgid ""
"Move to the bottom, right corner of the area you wish to include in the "
"frame, and press <b>CTRL+SHIFT+RIGHT BRACKET</b>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_frame.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:22-1
msgid ""
"A dialog box appears asking you if you wish to create a frame or a prompt. "
"Select to create a frame."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_frame.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:23-1
msgid ""
"A dialog appears to walk you through the creation of the frame. On the first "
"page, enter the name of the frame and select Next."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_frame.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:25-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note</b>: Frame names cannot contain spaces "
"or symbols. We recommend concatenating the names, capitalizing the start of "
"each word."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_frame.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:27-1
msgid ""
"The second page asks for a synopsis of the frame's purpose. Fill out the "
"information and select Next. This information is very important if others "
"are going to use your frames."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_frame.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:28-1
msgid ""
"The third page asks for a more detailed description of the frame's purpose. "
"Fill out the information and select Next. This information is very important "
"if others are going to use your frames."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_frame.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:29-1
msgid ""
"The fourth page prompts you to assign a keystroke to the frame. If you "
"choose to assign a keystroke, text within the frame is spoken when the "
"keystroke is pressed. This functionality is added as a frame event and can "
"be modified later."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_frame.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:30-1
msgid ""
"The fifth page prompts you to specify how JAWS will echo text newly written "
"within the frame. Select JAWS Screen Echo, Silent, Highlight, or All. These "
"settings correspond to using the current JAWS screen echo setting, or "
"specifying which screen echo setting to use. This functionality is added "
"through use of Frame Events. For information on what Frame Event is added "
"based on your selection, please refer to <a "
"href=\"Frame_Defaults.htm#events\">Default Frame Events</a>. After selecting "
"an option, select Finish to continue."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_frame.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:32-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Tip</b>: Move the JAWS cursor to a control "
"or window, and press <b>CTRL+SHIFT+LEFT BRACKET</b> twice quickly to set the "
"frame to the current control or window. Then fill in the information as "
"stated above."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_frame.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:33-1
msgid ""
"At this point, the frame is created, but not saved. Focus is on the frame, "
"and Frame Viewer is active. Press the <b>Applications</b> key to open the "
"context menu for the frame."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_frame.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:35-1
msgid "Select Save Changes from the menu to save the frame."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_frame.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:36-1
msgid "Select Properties to modify settings for the frame."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_frame.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:37-1
msgid ""
"If you select Exit Frames Mode without first saving the frame, a dialog "
"prompts you to save your changes."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_frame.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:39-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Tip</b>: Sighted users of JAWS may find it "
"easier and more straightforward to create a frame by opening Frame Viewer, "
"selecting Options, Create New Frame, and after filling in the information in "
"the Create a Frame dialogs, sizing and positioning the frame with the mouse. "
"By default, frames created in this manner are sized to the current control "
"or window."
msgstr ""

